                                                                                               authenticator                      Something that the claimant possesses and controls (typically a
                                                                                                                                  cryptographic module or password) that is used to authenticate
                                                                                                                                  the claimantâ€™s identity. This was previously referred to as a
                                                                                                                                  token.
                                                                                               authenticity                       The property of being genuine and being able to be verified and
                                                                                                                                  trusted; confidence in the validity of a transmission, message, or
                                                                                                                                  message originator. See authentication.
                                                                                               authorization                      Access privileges granted to a user, program, or process or the
                                                                                               [CNSSI 4009]                       act of granting those privileges.
                                                                                               authorization boundary             All components of an information system to be authorized for
                                                                                               [OMB A-130]                        operation by an authorizing official. This excludes separately
